# Mobile width convention — ShadiPlan

This is a mobile-first PWA. Every screen and every overlay (Sheet, Dialog,
Drawer, Popover) MUST follow the same responsive width behavior:

- Below ~430px viewport width (real mobile devices): full-bleed, edge to
  edge, no card border/shadow/margin.
- Above ~430px viewport width (desktop browser testing): constrained to a
  centered ~430px-wide column, with a border/shadow/rounded corners so it
  reads as an intentional mobile preview, not a broken desktop layout.

This behavior lives in two places and should never be reimplemented ad hoc:
- `MobileFrame` (src/components/mobile-frame.tsx) for page-level content
- The shared Sheet/Dialog/Drawer primitives in src/components/ui/ for any
  overlay, which apply the same max-w-[430px] mx-auto constraint

Before adding any new screen or overlay component, confirm it's built on
top of one of these two, not a fresh one-off layout. If a new kind of
overlay or layout primitive is genuinely needed, apply this same width
rule to it explicitly — do not let it default to unconstrained full-width
behavior.
